   <text>
      <body>
         
            
               <p>Susanna ('Suky') was born to <persName>
                            <ref target="/persons/pers2188.xml"/>Samuel</persName> and <persName>
                            <ref target="/persons/pers2193.xml"/>Susanna (Annesley) Wesley</persName> in
                     <placeName>South Ormsby, Lincolnshire</placeName> around <date when="1695">1695</date> (the exact date is unknown). On <date when="1718-01-11">Jan. 11,
                     1718</date> she was married to <persName>
                            <ref target="/persons/pers0660.xml"/>Richard Ellison</persName>, of <placeName>Epworth</placeName>, in
                     <placeName>Ackworth, Yorkshire</placeName> (where Susanna was apparently
                  serving as a maid or nanny). The couple had at least ten children, of whom four
                  lived to adulthood. <persName>
                            <ref target="/persons/pers0660.xml"/>Ellison</persName> was an abusive husband, leading Susanna to take the
                  children and move to <placeName>London</placeName> about <date when="1735">1735</date>. The couple were eventually reunited in
                     <placeName>London</placeName>, and there Susanna died on <date when="1764-12-11">Dec. 11, 1764</date> (four years after her husband). See
                  Clarke, <hi rend="italic">Memoirs</hi> (<date when="1823">1823</date>, 483–85;
                     <date when="1836">1836</date>, 2:271–74; <date when="1848">1848</date>,
                  523–26); and Maser, <hi rend="italic">Sisters</hi>, 30–36.</p>
            
         
